The various drivers use these Linux header files:

* user use linux-headers-legacy.tbz2
* user drivers use linux-headers-legacy-udrivers.tbz2
* kernel core sources use linux-headers-kernel.tbz2
* kernel drivers use these as well as linux-headers-kdrivers.tbz2

Thare (AFAIK) all linux 2.4.22 headers, but the various sets may
contain specific hacks for the Nexus kernel or userspace environment.
